						<summary>

						<p>Capital of a curved wooden <hi rend="italic">Pāru</hi> column in the Chennakēśava manchāla temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1667, Krōdhana, Vaiśākha ba. 10,</hi> corresponding to 1745 A.D., May 15, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It states that the temple and the carvings depicting scenes from Rāmāyaṇa (on the wooden column) were completed on the date specified.</p>						

